sense.notes:
) 
informality, fault. Y. Gitt. II, 44
a bot. זה זִיּוּפֹו מד"א such a document (written in day-time and signed by night) would be defective on account of a condition not perceptible from the document itself, opp. מזוייף מתוכו, v. זוּף I.

sense.definition:
festive season (cmp. מִקְרָא, מְאַרְעָא); 
‘Z’man’,
that section of the benediction on the entrance of a Festival which refers to the return of the festive season (שהחיינו והגיענו לזמן הזה …).

 (b. h.) 
to glisten (cmp. דנח) 
to be fat; to be greasy, foul (cmp. meanings of זהם, צחן, v. Ges. Thes. s. v. זנח);

 preced.) 
span (the spread fingers); 
distance from the little finger to the thumb of a spread hand.
